article.story: DAVIS, Calif. -- — Connor Sevilla had 17 points in UC Davis' 77-66 victory against Cal Poly on Thursday night. Sevilla shot 5 for 10 (3 for 6 from 3-point range) and 4 of 4 from the free-throw line for the Aggies (4-4, 1-0 Big West Conference). Pablo Tamba scored 14 points and added six rebounds and three blocks. Ty Johnson had 14 points and shot 6 of 21 from the field, including 1 for 4 from 3-point range, and went 1 for 3 from the line. Owen Koonce led the way for the Mustangs (5-5, 0-1) with 19 points. Cal Poly also got eight points from Kieran Elliott. Mac Riniker also had seven points, seven rebounds and three steals. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
